main event: Multiple luminous objects were observed by witnesses over several nights in Sequoia National Park, California.
interesting points: The objects were seen on three consecutive nights from August 25 to August 27, 1965., Witnesses described the objects as moving rapidly from northwest to southeast., The objects changed color and direction during the observation., Witnesses noted that the objects appeared much brighter than stars or known satellites., The observations lasted between 3 to 10 minutes each night.
sighted object: four luminous objects in the sky
